DURBAN - The body of a woman, believed to be in her late twenties, was discovered along a railway line on Garland Street in Temple Valley, Verulam this morning. Provincial police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, confirmed that a case of murder was opened at Verulam Police Station for investigation. “This morning at 9am, the body of an unknown woman believed to be in her late twenties was found along a railway line on Garland Street in Verulam with a stab wound on the neck,” said Mbele. Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) spokesperson, Prem Balram, said a member of RUSA was on patrol in the Verulam CBD yesterday when he was flagged down by a pedestrian who informed him of the discovery. Balram said RUSA officers proceeded to the location provided and discovered the body of a female in the overgrown grass. He said the woman was naked from below the waist. “Upon examination, the deceased was found to have sustained a stab wound to her neck. Her blood-soaked pants were located next to her body,” said Balram. Police said the motive for the killing is unknown.     THE MERCURY